optionally launch an instance of the robot (sim/real)
launch the flip_ptu_driver, 
roslaunch flir_ptu_driver ptu.launch port:=/dev/ttyS0 OR
roslaunch flir_ptu_driver ptu.launch port:=/dev/ttyUSB0, depending on how you 
are connected (I personaly prefer the serial port than the usb-fake-serial port)
reset the ptu (optional) (ROS_NAMESPACE=ptu) rosrun flir_ptu_driver cmd_angles 0 0
start the scanning!
(ROS_NAMESPACE=ptu) rosrun flir_ptu_driver cmd_scan
stop the scanning whenever you want with ctrl^C
